hf_response.name: FRM_ROUNDINGMODE_ACCESS_TYPE
hf_response.description: ROUNDINGMODE field is read‑write and may be updated by hardware.

hf_response.name: FRM_ROUNDINGMODE_LEGAL_VALUES
hf_response.spec_quote:
000 RNE Round to Nearest, ties to Even
001 RTZ Round towards Zero
010 RDN Round Down (towards -∞)
011 RUP Round Up (towards +∞)
100 RMM Round to Nearest, ties to Max Magnitude

hf_response.name: FRM_ROUNDINGMODE_CONTROLS_RESERVED_BEHAVIOR
hf_response.description: When a reserved rounding‑mode value is used, the behavior of dependent floating‑point instructions is reserved.
hf_response.spec_quote: The behavior of floating-point instructions that depend on rounding mode when executed with a reserved rounding mode is reserved, including both static reserved rounding modes (101-110) and dynamic reserved rounding modes (101-111).
